1223
01:17:58,207 --> 01:17:59,959
MARVIN: Get home to your mama, boy.

1224
01:18:00,047 --> 01:18:02,197
THUG 1: Biff!
THUG 2: Hurry, Biff!

1225
01:18:02,727 --> 01:18:04,638
MARTY: [Muffled] Let me out of here!

1226
01:18:04,727 --> 01:18:06,126
[Pounding and shouting]

1227
01:18:06,207 --> 01:18:07,765
Reginald, where are your keys?

1228
01:18:07,847 --> 01:18:09,963
MARTY: [Muffled] The keys are in the trunk.

1229
01:18:10,247 --> 01:18:13,159
MARVIN: Say that again?
MARTY: I said, the keys are in here.

1230
01:18:17,767 --> 01:18:19,359
LORRAINE: [Muffled] Let me go!

1231
01:18:26,327 --> 01:18:27,362
BIFF: [Muffled] Come on!

1232
01:18:29,567 --> 01:18:32,957
Hey you, get your damn hands off...

1233
01:18:33,327 --> 01:18:34,726
[Sighing]

1234
01:18:35,287 --> 01:18:37,437
I think you got the wrong car, McFly.

1235
01:18:39,047 --> 01:18:41,003
George, help me! Please!

1236
01:18:41,087 --> 01:18:44,557
Just turn around, McFly, and walk away.

1237
01:18:44,847 --> 01:18:46,917
LORRAINE: Please, George.
BIFF: Are you deaf?

1238
01:18:47,007 --> 01:18:48,998
BIFF: Close the door and beat it.

1239
01:18:49,167 --> 01:18:50,520
[Lorraine whimpering]

1240
01:18:51,487 --> 01:18:55,002
No, Biff. You leave her alone.

1241
01:18:55,647 --> 01:18:57,365
All right, McFly.

1242
01:19:00,487 --> 01:19:02,398
You're asking for it...

1243
01:19:02,567 --> 01:19:04,523
...and now you're going to get it.

1244
01:19:04,647 --> 01:19:05,636
[George groaning]

1245
01:19:05,727 --> 01:19:06,921
Stop it!

1246
01:19:07,727 --> 01:19:09,558
Biff, you'll break his arm!

1247
01:19:09,687 --> 01:19:11,040
[Gasping]

1248
01:19:11,327 --> 01:19:13,158
LORRAINE: Biff, no!

1249
01:19:13,327 --> 01:19:15,158
MARVIN: Give me a hand here, Reginald.

1250
01:19:15,727 --> 01:19:16,716
[Exclaiming]

1251
01:19:16,807 --> 01:19:18,923
Damn it, man! I sliced my hand!

1252
01:19:19,007 --> 01:19:20,486
- Whose are these?
- Mine.

1253
01:19:20,567 --> 01:19:22,398
Thanks. Thanks a lot.

1254
01:19:23,687 --> 01:19:25,917
You're going to break his arm!

1255
01:19:26,127 --> 01:19:29,244
Biff! Biff, leave him alone!

1256
01:19:29,327 --> 01:19:31,682
Let him go! Let him go!

1257
01:19:33,647 --> 01:19:35,205
[Biff laughing]

1258
01:19:36,367 --> 01:19:38,562
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

1259
01:19:45,607 --> 01:19:46,596
[Biff grunts]

1260
01:19:53,967 --> 01:19:55,446
[George panting]

1261
01:20:03,287 --> 01:20:05,118
Are you okay?

1262
01:20:08,807 --> 01:20:11,082
[Tender instrumental music]

1263
01:20:24,127 --> 01:20:26,038
Who is that guy?

1264
01:20:26,327 --> 01:20:28,158
That's George McFly.

1265
01:20:31,287 --> 01:20:33,039
That's George McFly?

1266
01:20:33,127 --> 01:20:34,526
Excuse me.

1267
01:20:36,807 --> 01:20:38,525
[Thunder rumbling]

1268
01:20:45,367 --> 01:20:46,800
The storm.

1269
01:20:48,687 --> 01:20:51,281
Guys, you got to get back in there
and finish the dance.

1270
01:20:51,367 --> 01:20:52,720
Look at Marvin's hand.

1271
01:20:52,807 --> 01:20:55,958
He can't play with this hand,
and we can't play without him.

1272
01:20:56,047 --> 01:20:57,480
Marvin, you got to play.

1273
01:20:57,567 --> 01:21:01,321
They kiss for the first time at the dance.
If there's no music, they can't dance.

1274
01:21:01,407 --> 01:21:05,036
If they can't dance and kiss,
then they can't fall in love and I'm history.

1275
01:21:05,127 --> 01:21:08,881
The dance is over unless you know
somebody that can play the guitar.

1276
01:21:09,007 --> 01:21:10,963
[Playing <i>Earth Angel</i>]

1277
01:21:15,847 --> 01:21:18,156
<i>This is for all you lovers out there.</i>

1278
01:21:20,527 --> 01:21:23,997
MARVIN: [Singing]
<i>"Earth Angel, Earth Angel</i>

1279
01:21:25,007 --> 01:21:27,157
<i>"Will you be mine</i>

1280
01:21:28,247 --> 01:21:30,522
<i>"My darling dear"</i>

1281
01:21:31,647 --> 01:21:33,683
LORRAINE:
George, aren't you going to kiss me?

1282
01:21:33,767 --> 01:21:35,644
I don't know.

1283
01:21:36,647 --> 01:21:39,002
Scram, McFly. I'm cutting in.

1284
01:21:39,167 --> 01:21:40,839
[Lorraine protesting]

1285
01:21:43,247 --> 01:21:45,283
[Playing dissonant notes]

1286
01:21:45,407 --> 01:21:48,399
<i>"Earth Angel, Earth Angel</i>

1287
01:21:49,447 --> 01:21:51,597
<i>"The one I adore"</i>

1288
01:21:51,687 --> 01:21:53,405
Hey, boy, you all right?

1289
01:21:54,687 --> 01:21:56,086
I can't play.

1290
01:21:56,207 --> 01:21:57,435
George!

1291
01:21:57,767 --> 01:21:59,519
[Boy laughing]

1292
01:21:59,887 --> 01:22:02,196
[Oppressive instrumental music]

1293
01:22:06,247 --> 01:22:08,283
[Ominous instrumental music]

1294
01:22:13,167 --> 01:22:14,156
[Boy laughing]

1295
01:22:14,247 --> 01:22:15,236
George!

1296
01:22:16,367 --> 01:22:17,561
George.

1297
01:22:20,567 --> 01:22:22,125
Excuse me.

1298
01:22:22,287 --> 01:22:23,481
[Boy grunts]

1299
01:22:24,327 --> 01:22:26,363
[Uplifting instrumental music]

1300
01:22:30,407 --> 01:22:33,205
MARVIN: [Singing]
<i>"The vision of your happiness</i>

1301
01:22:35,687 --> 01:22:38,565
<i>"Earth Angel, Earth Angel</i>

1302
01:22:39,327 --> 01:22:41,602
<i>"Please be mine</i>

1303
01:22:42,847 --> 01:22:44,803
<i>"My darling dear</i>

1304
01:22:45,127 --> 01:22:47,118
<i>"Love you for all time</i>

1305
01:22:48,807 --> 01:22:51,116
<i>"I'm just a fool</i>

1306
01:22:53,047 --> 01:22:55,322
<i>"A fool in love</i>

1307
01:22:57,287 --> 01:23:00,279
<i>"with you"</i>

1308
01:23:04,767 --> 01:23:06,405
[Crowd applauding]

1309
01:23:07,087 --> 01:23:10,796
MARVIN: Yeah, man, that was good.
Let's do another one.

1310
01:23:10,887 --> 01:23:12,764
No. I got to go.

1311
01:23:12,847 --> 01:23:15,839
Come on, man.
Let's do something that really cooks.

1312
01:23:16,287 --> 01:23:19,245
Something that cooks.

1313
01:23:19,527 --> 01:23:21,119
[Cheering]

1314
01:23:24,127 --> 01:23:26,163
MARTY: All right.
MARVIN: <i>All right!</i>

1315
01:23:30,007 --> 01:23:31,326
<i>All right.</i>

1316
01:23:32,207 --> 01:23:35,483
<i>All right, this is an oldie, but...</i>

1317
01:23:37,407 --> 01:23:41,002
<i>Well, it's an oldie where I come from.</i>

1318
01:23:42,567 --> 01:23:44,762
All right, listen, this is a blues riff in B.

1319
01:23:44,847 --> 01:23:47,725
Watch me for the changes,
and try and keep up, okay?

1320
01:23:48,087 --> 01:23:49,839
[Playing <i>Johnny B. Goode</i>]

1321
01:24:04,007 --> 01:24:06,885
<i>"Way down in Louisiana</i>
<i>Down in New Orleans</i>

1322
01:24:06,967 --> 01:24:09,879
<i>"Way back up in the woods</i>
<i>among the evergreens</i>

1323
01:24:09,967 --> 01:24:12,527
<i>"There stood a log cabin</i>
<i>made of earth and wood</i>

1324
01:24:12,607 --> 01:24:15,121
<i>"Where lived a country boy</i>
<i>name of Johnny B. Goode</i>

1325
01:24:15,207 --> 01:24:17,482
<i>"He never ever learned</i>
<i>to read or write so well</i>

1326
01:24:17,567 --> 01:24:20,206
<i>"He could play the guitar</i>
<i>just like he's ringin' a bell</i>

1327
01:24:20,287 --> 01:24:24,121
<i>"Go go</i>
<i>Go Johnny go, go</i>

1328
01:24:24,567 --> 01:24:27,081
<i>"Go Johnny, go, go, go</i>

1329
01:24:27,367 --> 01:24:29,005
<i>"Go Johnny go, go"</i>

1330
01:24:29,087 --> 01:24:31,362
George, I heard you laid out Biff.
Nice going.

1331
01:24:31,447 --> 01:24:33,642
You ever think of
running for class president?

1332
01:24:33,727 --> 01:24:36,036
MARTY: [Singing] <i>"Johnny B. Goode</i>

1333
01:24:38,287 --> 01:24:40,562
<i>"Go Johnny go, go</i>

1334
01:24:40,927 --> 01:24:43,487
<i>"Go Johnny go, go, go</i>

1335
01:24:43,567 --> 01:24:46,161
<i>"Go Johnny go, go</i>

1336
01:24:46,247 --> 01:24:49,000
<i>"Go Johnny go, go, go</i>

1337
01:24:49,647 --> 01:24:51,524
<i>"Johnny B. Goode"</i>

1338
01:24:53,887 --> 01:24:56,560
Chuck! Chuck, it's Marvin.

1339
01:24:56,647 --> 01:24:59,115
Your cousin, Marvin Berry?

1340
01:24:59,207 --> 01:25:01,846
You know that new sound
you're looking for?

1341
01:25:01,927 --> 01:25:03,963
Well, listen to this.

1342
01:25:25,207 --> 01:25:27,004
[Music growing wilder]

1343
01:25:33,247 --> 01:25:35,477
[Marty playing heavy metal riffs]

1344
01:25:48,407 --> 01:25:49,522
[Feedback]

1345
01:25:53,127 --> 01:25:55,083
[Playing sustained high-pitch note]

1346
01:25:55,607 --> 01:25:57,404
[Amplifiers humming]

1347
01:26:10,407 --> 01:26:12,875
<i>I guess you guys aren't ready for that yet...</i>

1348
01:26:14,247 --> 01:26:16,124
<i>... but your kids are going to love it.</i>

1349
01:26:16,567 --> 01:26:18,523
[Jazz playing faintly]

1350
01:26:20,167 --> 01:26:21,361
Lorraine.

1351
01:26:21,527 --> 01:26:24,087
Marty, that was very interesting music.

1352
01:26:24,807 --> 01:26:26,035
Yeah.

1353
01:26:26,127 --> 01:26:29,563
I hope you don't mind, but George
asked if he could take me home.

1354
01:26:29,647 --> 01:26:34,118
Great! Good. Good, Lorraine.
I had a feeling about you two.

1355
01:26:34,487 --> 01:26:36,000
I have a feeling, too.

1356
01:26:36,727 --> 01:26:38,558
Listen, I got to go, but...

1357
01:26:38,647 --> 01:26:42,686
...I wanted to tell you that
it's been educational.

1358
01:26:43,687 --> 01:26:45,803
LORRAINE: Marty, will we ever see you again?

1359
01:26:47,207 --> 01:26:48,356
I guarantee it.

1360
01:26:48,447 --> 01:26:51,678
Well, Marty, I want to thank you
for all your good advice.

1361
01:26:51,767 --> 01:26:54,156
I'll never forget it.

1362
01:26:54,727 --> 01:26:56,206
Right, George.

1363
01:26:57,567 --> 01:27:00,923
Well, good luck, you guys.

1364
01:27:02,327 --> 01:27:03,601
[Marty exclaims]

1365
01:27:04,727 --> 01:27:06,479
One other thing.

1366
01:27:06,567 --> 01:27:08,478
<i>If you guys ever have kids...</i>

1367
01:27:08,567 --> 01:27:10,876
<i>... and one of them,</i>
<i>when he's eight years old...</i>

1368
01:27:10,967 --> 01:27:13,879
...accidentally sets fire
to the living room rug...

1369
01:27:15,167 --> 01:27:16,680
...go easy on him.

1370
01:27:17,647 --> 01:27:18,875
Okay.

1371
01:27:23,567 --> 01:27:26,684
Marty. Such a nice name.

1372
01:27:32,007 --> 01:27:33,804
Damn! Where is that kid?

1373
01:27:34,767 --> 01:27:37,042
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

1374
01:27:37,127 --> 01:27:38,321
Damn!

1375
01:27:40,687 --> 01:27:42,040
Damn! Damn!

1376
01:27:44,967 --> 01:27:46,480
[Brakes squealing]

1377
01:27:49,527 --> 01:27:52,280
DOC: You're late!
Do you have no concept of time?

1378
01:27:52,367 --> 01:27:54,642
Hey, come on. I had to change.

1379
01:27:54,727 --> 01:27:57,480
Do you think I'm going back
in that zoot suit?

1380
01:27:57,607 --> 01:28:00,121
The old man really came through.
It worked.

1381
01:28:00,247 --> 01:28:02,238
He laid out Biff in one punch.

1382
01:28:02,327 --> 01:28:06,206
I didn't know he had it in him.
He's never stood up to Biff in his life.

1383
01:28:07,847 --> 01:28:11,157
- Never?
- No. Why? What's the matter?

1384
01:28:11,767 --> 01:28:12,995
All right!

1385
01:28:13,247 --> 01:28:15,317
Let's set your destination time.

1386
01:28:18,127 --> 01:28:19,560
[Machine beeping]

1387
01:28:19,887 --> 01:28:22,117
DOC: This is the exact time you left.

1388
01:28:22,527 --> 01:28:25,803
<i>Let's send you back at exactly</i>
<i>the same time.</i>

1389
01:28:28,607 --> 01:28:30,563
It'll be like you never left.

1390
01:28:32,367 --> 01:28:36,485
Now, I painted a white line
on the street way over there.

1391
01:28:36,687 --> 01:28:38,484
That's where you'll start from.

1392
01:28:38,567 --> 01:28:40,762
I've calculated the precise distance...

1393
01:28:40,847 --> 01:28:43,441
...taking into account
the acceleration speed...

1394
01:28:43,527 --> 01:28:47,600
...and wind resistance retroactive
from the moment the lightning strikes...

1395
01:28:47,887 --> 01:28:52,358
...which will be in exactly
7 minutes and 22 seconds.

1396
01:28:52,567 --> 01:28:54,876
When this alarm goes off, you hit the gas.

1397
01:28:54,967 --> 01:28:56,195
Right.

1398
01:28:56,607 --> 01:28:58,837
[Dramatic instrumental music]

1399
01:29:02,487 --> 01:29:05,559
Well, I guess that's everything.

1400
01:29:09,447 --> 01:29:11,756
- Thanks.
- Thank you.

1401
01:29:16,927 --> 01:29:18,804
DOC: See you in about 30 years.

1402
01:29:20,567 --> 01:29:22,205
I hope so.

1403
01:29:23,447 --> 01:29:25,005
Don't worry!

1404
01:29:25,607 --> 01:29:27,245
<i>As long as you hit that wire...</i>

1405
01:29:27,327 --> 01:29:30,285
...with the connecting hook
at precisely 88 miles an hour...

1406
01:29:30,367 --> 01:29:33,200
...the instant the lightning
strikes the tower...

1407
01:29:35,567 --> 01:29:37,683
DOC: Everything will be fine.
MARTY: Right.

1408
01:29:44,727 --> 01:29:46,285
[Thunder rumbling]

1409
01:29:46,407 --> 01:29:49,922
- What's the meaning of this?
- You'll find out in 30 years.

1410
01:29:50,007 --> 01:29:51,998
It's about the future, isn't it?

1411
01:29:52,087 --> 01:29:54,681
DOC: Information about the future.
MARTY: Wait a minute.

1412
01:29:54,767 --> 01:29:56,644
I warned you about this, kid.

1413
01:29:56,727 --> 01:29:59,400
The consequences could be disastrous!

1414
01:29:59,527 --> 01:30:01,836
Doc, that's a risk
you're going to have to take.

1415
01:30:01,927 --> 01:30:04,999
- Your life depends on it!
- No!

1416
01:30:05,087 --> 01:30:08,284
I refuse to accept the responsibility.

1417
01:30:08,567 --> 01:30:11,127
In that case, I'll tell you straight out.

1418
01:30:12,207 --> 01:30:14,243
[Thunder crashing]

1419
01:30:15,047 --> 01:30:16,366
Great Scott!

1420
01:30:19,167 --> 01:30:20,839
[Thunder clapping]

1421
01:30:24,007 --> 01:30:26,919
You get the cable,
I'll throw the rope down to you.

1422
01:30:27,007 --> 01:30:29,077
MARTY: Right! I got it!

1423
01:30:56,007 --> 01:30:57,645
[Wind howling]

1424
01:30:59,007 --> 01:31:00,281
[Gasping]

1425
01:31:01,487 --> 01:31:02,715
Doc!

1426
01:31:10,047 --> 01:31:13,960
DOC: Come on, come on. Let's go!
MARTY: All right! Take it up!

1427
01:31:17,287 --> 01:31:18,322
Go!

1428
01:31:25,127 --> 01:31:26,116
Doc!

1429
01:31:26,207 --> 01:31:27,196
[Shouting indistinctly]

1430
01:31:27,287 --> 01:31:30,643
I have to tell you about the future.

1431
01:31:30,727 --> 01:31:34,845
DOC: What?
MARTY: I have to tell you about the future!

1432
01:31:35,007 --> 01:31:36,281
What?

1433
01:31:36,367 --> 01:31:40,883
On the night I go back in time you get...

1434
01:31:41,167 --> 01:31:42,646
[Clock bells ringing]

1435
01:31:44,367 --> 01:31:45,641
Doc!

1436
01:31:51,007 --> 01:31:52,520
[Doc screaming]

1437
01:31:54,527 --> 01:31:55,403
Go!

1438
01:31:56,407 --> 01:31:58,557
- No, Doc!
- Look at the time!

1439
01:31:58,847 --> 01:32:00,917
You've got less than four minutes.

1440
01:32:01,007 --> 01:32:02,645
<i>Please, hurry!</i>

1441
01:32:02,727 --> 01:32:04,240
[Dramatic instrumental music]

1442
01:32:04,327 --> 01:32:05,840
[Bell ringing]

1443
01:32:13,807 --> 01:32:15,081
DOC: Yeah!

1444
01:33:06,127 --> 01:33:09,278
Damn it, Doc!
Why did you have to tear up that letter?

1445
01:33:09,367 --> 01:33:11,244
If I only had more time.

1446
01:33:14,127 --> 01:33:16,402
Wait a minute. I got all the time I want.

1447
01:33:16,487 --> 01:33:19,923
I got a time machine.
I can just go back early and warn him.

1448
01:33:20,007 --> 01:33:22,077
Okay. Ten minutes ought to do it.

1449
01:33:23,927 --> 01:33:26,122
<i>Okay. Time circuit's on.</i>

1450
01:33:26,447 --> 01:33:29,007
Flux capacitor, fluxing.

1451
01:33:29,447 --> 01:33:31,438
Engine running. All right.

1452
01:33:31,567 --> 01:33:33,444
[Engine stops suddenly]

1453
01:33:34,167 --> 01:33:36,476
No. No, no.

1454
01:33:36,567 --> 01:33:39,798
Come on. Come on. Not this time.

1455
01:33:58,927 --> 01:34:00,360
[Doc screaming]

1456
01:34:05,887 --> 01:34:07,684
[Engine clicking]

1457
01:34:12,687 --> 01:34:13,676
[Grunts]

1458
01:34:47,287 --> 01:34:48,515
MARTY: Come on.

1459
01:34:48,607 --> 01:34:50,165
[Alarm ringing]

1460
01:34:50,527 --> 01:34:53,166
Here we go. Here we go.
This time. Come on.

1461
01:34:54,767 --> 01:34:57,520
Please. Please. Come on!

1462
01:34:57,927 --> 01:34:58,882
[Shouts]

1463
01:34:58,967 --> 01:34:59,956
[Engine starts]

1464
01:35:02,967 --> 01:35:04,195
[Tires squealing]

1465
01:35:17,647 --> 01:35:18,636
[Grunts]

1466
01:35:38,727 --> 01:35:40,285
[Screaming]

1467
01:35:51,487 --> 01:35:53,682
[Dramatic instrumental music]

1468
01:36:19,847 --> 01:36:21,360
[Screaming]

1469
01:36:31,847 --> 01:36:33,166
Doc.

1470
01:36:50,807 --> 01:36:53,002
[Wind blowing]

1471
01:37:19,487 --> 01:37:21,443
[Doc shouting gleefully]

1472
01:37:31,327 --> 01:37:32,885
[Helicopter whirring]

1473
01:37:45,927 --> 01:37:47,679
[Music playing on radio]

1474
01:37:50,647 --> 01:37:52,000
[Explosive crashing]

1475
01:37:54,087 --> 01:37:55,679
[Tires squealing]

1476
01:38:05,407 --> 01:38:07,398
Crazy drunk driver.

1477
01:38:17,447 --> 01:38:18,721
[Marty exclaims]

1478
01:38:21,767 --> 01:38:23,758
All right. Fred.

1479
01:38:25,527 --> 01:38:28,121
You look great. Everything looks great.

1480
01:38:28,207 --> 01:38:29,356
[Marty panting]

1481
01:38:29,447 --> 01:38:30,436
<i>1:24.</i>

1482
01:38:30,527 --> 01:38:33,280
I still got time. I'm coming, Doc!

1483
01:38:34,967 --> 01:38:36,241
[Engine dies]

1484
01:38:36,767 --> 01:38:39,042
No! No, not again!

1485
01:38:39,127 --> 01:38:41,516
Come on! Come on!

1486
01:38:41,607 --> 01:38:43,325
[Tires squealing]

1487
01:38:46,767 --> 01:38:48,325
[Terrorists shouting indistinctly]

1488
01:38:54,567 --> 01:38:55,886
Libyans.

1489
01:38:59,607 --> 01:39:01,518
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

1490
01:39:17,527 --> 01:39:18,562
MARTY: <i>No!</i>

1491
01:39:19,847 --> 01:39:21,121
<i>Bastards!</i>

1492
01:39:34,047 --> 01:39:35,321
TERRORIST: Go!

1493
01:39:36,287 --> 01:39:37,800
[Tires squealing]

1494
01:39:39,647 --> 01:39:41,080
[Gunshots firing]

1495
01:40:08,327 --> 01:40:10,397
MARTY: Doc! Doc!

1496
01:40:10,807 --> 01:40:12,399
[Marty sobbing]

1497
01:40:12,487 --> 01:40:14,637
[Tender instrumental music]

1498
01:40:17,087 --> 01:40:17,963
MARTY: No!

1499
01:40:32,007 --> 01:40:33,406
You're alive.

1500
01:40:42,287 --> 01:40:43,766
Bulletproof vest?

1501
01:40:45,087 --> 01:40:46,964
How did you know?

1502
01:40:47,447 --> 01:40:50,007
<i>I never got a chance to tell you.</i>

1503
01:41:02,807 --> 01:41:06,641
What about all that talk
about screwing up future events?

1504
01:41:06,767 --> 01:41:08,644
The space-time continuum?

1505
01:41:09,207 --> 01:41:11,960
Well, I figured, what the hell.

1506
01:41:12,207 --> 01:41:14,402
[Uplifting instrumental music]

1507
01:41:21,807 --> 01:41:23,604
MARTY: So how far ahead are you going?

1508
01:41:23,687 --> 01:41:26,645
About 30 years. It's a nice round number.

1509
01:41:26,727 --> 01:41:28,763
Look me up when you get there, all right?

1510
01:41:28,847 --> 01:41:30,838
Guess I'll be about 47.

1511
01:41:31,087 --> 01:41:32,156
I will.

1512
01:41:32,687 --> 01:41:33,722
MARTY: Take care.

1513
01:41:34,807 --> 01:41:35,796
You, too.

1514
01:41:36,007 --> 01:41:38,237
Right. Bye-bye, Einie.

1515
01:41:38,687 --> 01:41:41,440
MARTY: And watch that re-entry.
It's a little bumpy.

1516
01:41:42,287 --> 01:41:43,242
You bet.

1517
01:42:03,167 --> 01:42:04,646
[Explosive crashing]

1518
01:42:06,887 --> 01:42:08,639
[Dog barking]

1519
01:42:20,247 --> 01:42:21,999
[Radio plays <i>Back In Time</i>]

1520
01:42:45,887 --> 01:42:47,240
What a nightmare.

1521
01:42:57,967 --> 01:43:01,164
LINDA: If Paul calls, tell him I'm working
at the boutique late.

1522
01:43:01,247 --> 01:43:03,238
DAVID:
Linda, I'm not your answering service...

1523
01:43:03,327 --> 01:43:06,683
...and somebody named Greg or Craig
<i>called you just a little while ago.</i>

1524
01:43:06,767 --> 01:43:10,646
LINDA: Which one was it?
DAVID: I can't keep up with your boyfriends.

1525
01:43:11,047 --> 01:43:12,036
[Marty calls]

1526
01:43:13,127 --> 01:43:14,640
MARTY: What the hell is this?

1527
01:43:15,407 --> 01:43:16,476
Breakfast.

1528
01:43:17,007 --> 01:43:19,157
DAVID: Did you sleep in your clothes again?

1529
01:43:19,407 --> 01:43:20,601
Yeah. L...

1530
01:43:21,727 --> 01:43:23,957
What are you wearing, Dave?

1531
01:43:24,327 --> 01:43:25,396
Marty...

1532
01:43:25,927 --> 01:43:28,043
...I always wear a suit to the office.

1533
01:43:28,727 --> 01:43:30,399
DAVID: You all right?
MARTY: Yeah.

1534
01:43:31,247 --> 01:43:33,363
MRS. MCFLY: We need a rematch.
MR. MCFLY: A rematch?

1535
01:43:33,447 --> 01:43:35,517
- Why? Were you cheating?
- No.

1536
01:43:35,607 --> 01:43:37,279
- Hello.
- Good morning.

1537
01:43:39,367 --> 01:43:40,800
Mom! Dad!

1538
01:43:41,167 --> 01:43:43,601
MR. MCFLY: Hit your head?
MRS. MCFLY: Are you okay?

1539
01:43:43,687 --> 01:43:46,679
You guys look great.
Mom, you look so thin.

1540
01:43:46,967 --> 01:43:49,356
Why, thank you, Marty. George!

1541
01:43:50,807 --> 01:43:52,479
Good morning, sleepyhead.

1542
01:43:53,687 --> 01:43:56,326
MRS. MCFLY: Good morning, kids.
DAVID AND LINDA: 'Morning.

1543
01:43:56,447 --> 01:43:58,881
LINDA: Marty, I almost forgot.
Jennifer Parker called.

1544
01:43:58,967 --> 01:44:02,403
I sure like her. She is such a sweet girl.

1545
01:44:02,927 --> 01:44:04,963
Isn't tonight the night of the big date?

1546
01:44:05,047 --> 01:44:06,799
What? What, Ma?

1547
01:44:06,887 --> 01:44:10,721
Aren't you going up to the lake?
You've been planning it for two weeks.

1548
01:44:10,927 --> 01:44:13,361
We talked about this.
How can I go to the lake?

1549
01:44:13,567 --> 01:44:14,636
The car's wrecked.

1550
01:44:14,727 --> 01:44:16,160
MR. MCFLY: Wrecked?
DAVID: Wrecked?

1551
01:44:16,327 --> 01:44:18,443
When did this happen? Why wasn't I told?

1552
01:44:18,527 --> 01:44:21,963
MR. MCFLY: I'm sure the car is fine.
DAVID: Why am I the last to know?

1553
01:44:22,287 --> 01:44:25,006
MR. MCFLY: See? There's Biff out there
waxing it now.

1554
01:44:25,647 --> 01:44:29,799
Now, Biff, I want to make sure we get
two coats of wax, not just one.

1555
01:44:29,887 --> 01:44:33,846
- I'm just finishing up the second coat now.
- Now, Biff, don't con me.

1556
01:44:35,447 --> 01:44:37,278
I'm sorry, Mr. McFly.

1557
01:44:37,447 --> 01:44:40,200
I meant I was just starting
on the second coat.

1558
01:44:40,927 --> 01:44:43,043
Biff. What a character.

1559
01:44:43,207 --> 01:44:45,516
<i>Always trying to get away with something.</i>

1560
01:44:45,607 --> 01:44:48,485
<i>I've had to stay on top of Biff</i>
<i>ever since high school.</i>

1561
01:44:48,567 --> 01:44:52,480
MR. MCFLY: But, if it wasn't for him...
MRS. MCFLY: We'd never have fallen in love.

1562
01:44:54,167 --> 01:44:56,635
Mr. McFly! Mr. McFly, this just arrived.

1563
01:44:56,807 --> 01:44:59,367
Hi, Marty. I think it's your new book.

1564
01:45:02,007 --> 01:45:04,282
Honey! Your first novel.

1565
01:45:05,727 --> 01:45:10,596
MR. MCFLY: I've always told you, if you put your
mind to it, you can accomplish anything.

1566
01:45:10,767 --> 01:45:14,237
Marty, here's your keys.
You're all waxed up, ready for tonight.

1567
01:45:14,487 --> 01:45:15,397
Keys?

1568
01:45:26,847 --> 01:45:28,883
[Tender instrumental music]

1569
01:45:31,247 --> 01:45:33,602
- How about a ride, mister?
- Jennifer!

1570
01:45:35,207 --> 01:45:37,084
Are you a sight for sore eyes.

1571
01:45:37,447 --> 01:45:39,085
MARTY: Let me look at you.

1572
01:45:39,567 --> 01:45:42,320
Marty, you're acting like
you haven't seen me in a week.

1573
01:45:42,407 --> 01:45:43,476
I haven't.

1574
01:45:44,327 --> 01:45:45,396
You okay?

1575
01:45:46,247 --> 01:45:47,999
Is everything all right?

1576
01:45:50,607 --> 01:45:51,642
MARTY: Yeah.

1577
01:45:53,807 --> 01:45:55,399
Everything is great.

1578
01:45:58,247 --> 01:45:59,919
[Explosive crashing]

1579
01:46:01,087 --> 01:46:02,520
[Brakes screeching]

1580
01:46:09,207 --> 01:46:10,117
Marty!

1581
01:46:11,447 --> 01:46:13,438
You've got to come back with me!

1582
01:46:14,047 --> 01:46:16,197
- Where?
- Back to the future.

1583
01:46:20,807 --> 01:46:22,559
What are you doing, Doc?

1584
01:46:23,847 --> 01:46:24,996
I need fuel.

1585
01:46:28,167 --> 01:46:30,237
Go ahead. Quick! Get in the car.

1586
01:46:30,567 --> 01:46:34,845
No, no. I just got here. Jennifer's here.
We're taking the new truck for a spin.

1587
01:46:34,927 --> 01:46:37,680
DOC: Bring her along. This concerns her, too.

1588
01:46:37,807 --> 01:46:41,163
What are you talking about?
What happens to us in the future?

1589
01:46:41,447 --> 01:46:44,280
- Do we become assholes or something?
- No, Marty.

1590
01:46:44,367 --> 01:46:47,564
Both you and Jennifer turn out fine.
It's your kids, Marty.

1591
01:46:47,647 --> 01:46:49,797
Something has got to be done
about your kids.

1592
01:46:55,927 --> 01:46:58,839
We better back up.
We don't have enough road to get up to 88.

1593
01:46:58,927 --> 01:47:02,397
Roads? Where we're going,
we don't need roads.

1594
01:47:04,127 --> 01:47:05,560
[Jets firing]

1595
01:47:14,367 --> 01:47:16,756
[<i>Back In Time</i> playing]